14/02/2005
ATHENS, Greece -- A British journalist and four Greek climbers have been killed in an avalanche in the southern Peloponnese Mountains in Greece. Athens-based reporter Diana Seale and the others were in a group of 28 on Mount Menalos when they were caught in the avalanche. The 23 other climbers escaped with minor injuries.
In other news, the head of the Greek Orthodox Church, Archbishop Christodoulos, announced Friday (11 February) that he would call an urgent meeting of the top clergy -- the Holy Synod -- by the end of this month. The extraordinary convention will focus on corruption scandals involving the Church.(BBC - 14/02/05; Kathimerini, MPA - 12/02/05) 
